{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T19:23:37.683913", "user": "explain Newton's first law", "nova": "Newton's first law, also known as the law of inertia, states that an object at rest stays at rest and an object in motion stays in motion with the same speed and in the same direction unless acted upon by an unbalanced force. This means that objects will stay still or keep moving without any external forces acting on them. It's important to note that this first law is a fundamental principle of physics and forms the basis for understanding how our universe operates at its most basic level."}
