{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.844573", "user": "what is the speed of light", "nova": "The speed of light in vacuum is about 299,792,458 meters per second (roughly 300,000 km/s), the universal speed limit."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.845209", "user": "what is mitosis", "nova": "Mitosis is cell division that produces two identical daughter cells, essential for growth, repair, and asexual reproduction."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.845888", "user": "define superfluous", "nova": "A superfluous item, like a necklace or hat you don't need because everything else matches perfectly, isn't necessary for your outfit but still takes up space and adds to its weight. They might be considered unnecessary in terms of practicality but can be seen as valuable possessions that make an item feel complete."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.846549", "user": "explain Newton's first law", "nova": "Newton's first law, also known as the law of inertia, states that an object at rest stays at rest and an object in motion stays in motion with the same speed and in the same direction unless acted upon by an unbalanced force. This means that objects will stay still or keep moving without any external forces acting on them. It's important to note that this first law is a fundamental principle of physics and forms the basis for understanding how our universe operates at its most basic level."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.847219", "user": "what is a black hole", "nova": "A black hole is a region of spacetime where gravity is so strong that nothing, not even light, can escape its pull."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.847870", "user": "what is photosynthesis", "nova": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water into glucose and oxygen, producing energy and releasing oxygen."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.848512", "user": "what is the speed of light", "nova": "The speed of light in vacuum is about 299,792,458 meters per second (roughly 300,000 km/s), the universal speed limit."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.849145", "user": "what is mitosis", "nova": "Mitosis is cell division that produces two identical daughter cells, essential for growth, repair, and asexual reproduction."}
