{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.850583", "user": "what is 15 percent of 200", "nova": "To calculate what 15 percent of 200 is, you can multiply 200 by 0.15 (since 15 percent is equivalent to 15 out of 100 or 0.15).\n\nSo:\n\n\\[ \\text{Result} = 200 \\times 0.15 = 30 \\]\n\nTherefore, 15 percent of 200 is 30."}
