{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.851879", "user": "why is the sky blue", "nova": "The sky appears blue because Earth's atmosphere scatters shorter-wavelength (blue) light more than longer wavelengths (red), causing the blue light to scatter throughout the sky, making it appear as if the sky itself is blue rather than reflecting the sun directly. This phenomenon is known as Rayleigh scattering."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:44.852526", "user": "explain Newton's first law", "nova": "Newton's First Law of Motion states that an object at rest stays at rest unless acted upon by an external force, and an object in motion will stay in motion with the same speed and in the same direction unless acted upon by an external force. This law is also known as the law of inertia, which means it describes how objects resist changes to their state of motion."}
