{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.194910", "user": "Explain: Do not call it success just because train loss improved.", "nova": "Do not call it success just because train loss improved."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.195355", "user": "Explain: How do you know if a model is memorizing instead of learning?", "nova": "How do you know if a model is memorizing instead of learning?"}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.195796", "user": "Explain: Memorization repeats seen strings.", "nova": "Memorization repeats seen strings."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.196236", "user": "Explain: Compare held-out behavior, not only training loss.", "nova": "Compare held-out behavior, not only training loss."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.196678", "user": "Explain: If it answers training examples but fails new ones, memorization is likely.", "nova": "If it answers training examples but fails new ones, memorization is likely."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.197137", "user": "Explain: Do not use the training set as proof of learning.", "nova": "Do not use the training set as proof of learning."}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-26T23:39:45.197584", "user": "Explain: A claim needs comparison and measurement.", "nova": "A claim needs comparison and measurement."}
